  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA3">
<l>pāraḷavu mōraṭivait tōraṭiyum pāruṭutta</l>
<l>nīraḷavuñ cella nimirntatē – cūruruviṟ</l>
<l>pēyaḷavu kaṇṭa perumā ṉaṟikilē</l>
<l>ṉīyaḷavu kaṇṭa neṟi</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Placing one foot upto the measure of the earth, he stretched to go</l>
<l>with one foot upto the measure of the water that envelops the earth, the great lord</l>
<l>who saw the measure of the demon<note>Here one may wonder whether to take pēy, the usual designation of a female demon and often referring to Pūtanā who gave her breast to Kṛṣṇa, as a reference to Māvali from whom the dwarf took the world.</note> in fearful form. I don’t know</l>
<l>a path<note>Here neṟi appears to used metaphorical in the sense of āṟu, “way”, which is not one of the standard transfers of meaning.</note> to see your measure.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
